President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, authorizing federal aid to assist with response efforts following the explosions on April 15, 2013. The Department of Homeland Security's Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) will coordinate disaster relief efforts to alleviate hardship and provide necessary assistance. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to lessen the impacts of the emergency. Federal funding for emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.